@39137 = ~I thank you, <GABBER>, both for the woman's sake  - and my own peace of mind.  Even as a priestess of Ilmater, the poor woman has suffered enough.  Please, accept these - the wand I fashioned from the oak of Kuldahar, and it is not much, but it may help you in your quest.  The other items may prove of more use.~
@39141 = ~Oh, no, no, <GABBER>.  I give these to you *for* Kuldahar's sake.   The people of Kuldahar who remain have more than enough magic at their disposal - I wish these items to go where they will do the North the greatest good, and that is with *you.*  Now, please, accept this - as your duty, not a reward.~
@39143 = ~Welcome back, <GABBER>!  You have my gratitude... and the gratitude of all Kuldahar - why, I thought your battle in the Western Pass nothing short of epic, but your efforts here in Kuldahar threaten to outshine even your past heroics.  If you keep this up, the bards shall be hard-pressed to put your deeds to verse!~
@39149 = ~Well met again, <GABBER>.  How may I help you?~
@39150 = ~Jermsy, please!  It is the truth - I recognize them!  <GABBER> saved my life within the Ice Temple!  Lower your bow - and save your arrows for your enemies.~
@39169 = ~I'm <GABBER> - we come in peace.  Oswald brought us here to help you stop the Legion of the Chimera.~
